stories.contents:
Trying to ride your bike in Rochester? Even if it’s not winter, you’re still going to have some issues. Some residents living in the city have expressed these problems by using Yellr, a citizen engagement app. 

According to the City of Rochester website, “the City of Rochester is dedicated to making this a world-class bicycling community.” Since the summer of 2011, 45 lane miles of on-street bicycle facilities have been installed with more planned to come. 

“I would love to bike to work, but if I did I would have to ride on the sidewalk,” said an anonymous user.

Another user pointed out the bike lane on Monroe Ave near Alexander Street. “Cars close to bike path,” they commented. Not enough bike lanes was another top concern, along with dangers in sharing the road.
